        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2204512718" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8742632915596709122">Number two in the Warlord series.<br/>This is the warts and all story of Arthur, Guinevere, Sir Lancelot and the rest of the round table knights.<br/>There is nothing cosy and romantic about this tale. Lancelot is a narcissistic pig. Guinevere has delusions of grandeur and Arthur wants nothing more than to be a farmer.<br/>The usual suspects, greed, power, sex, revenge and religion, keep getting in the way of Arthur&apos;s aspirations of becoming a farmer.<br/>The game&apos;s afoot so unleash the dogs of war. And nobody does</span>
  <span id="freeText8742632915596709122" style="display:none">Number two in the Warlord series.<br />This is the warts and all story of Arthur, Guinevere, Sir Lancelot and the rest of the round table knights.<br />There is nothing cosy and romantic about this tale. Lancelot is a narcissistic pig. Guinevere has delusions of grandeur and Arthur wants nothing more than to be a farmer.<br />The usual suspects, greed, power, sex, revenge and religion, keep getting in the way of Arthur's aspirations of becoming a farmer.<br />The game's afoot so unleash the dogs of war. And nobody does this better than Arthur. <br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/12542.Bernard_Cornwell" title="Bernard Cornwell" rel="nofollow noopener">Bernard Cornwell</a> never fails to entertain. He takes a thread of known history and a bit of mythology, adds some literary licence and creates a book you can't put down. <br />If you are looking for characters that will elicit emotional responses from you, you will find them all here.<br /><br />Highly recommended for lovers of historical fiction. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8742632915596709122" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
