              <span id="reviewTextContainer4059672266" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2547725267786552954">This one has a slow start, but gradually picks up speed. Part way through the book, I realized I don&apos;t much like Arthur. He puts his trust in the wrong people and makes the wrong decisions, with disastrous results. He&apos;s an extremely good fighter, but not such a good thinker. Thank goodness for the trustworthy people in his life like Derfel, Galahad, Merlin, and Nimue. <br/><br/>Once past the slow start, it&apos;s an excellent story, but the last quarter of the book took quite the turn and I had a hard time put</span>
  <span id="freeText2547725267786552954" style="display:none">This one has a slow start, but gradually picks up speed. Part way through the book, I realized I don't much like Arthur. He puts his trust in the wrong people and makes the wrong decisions, with disastrous results. He's an extremely good fighter, but not such a good thinker. Thank goodness for the trustworthy people in his life like Derfel, Galahad, Merlin, and Nimue. <br /><br />Once past the slow start, it's an excellent story, but the last quarter of the book took quite the turn and I had a hard time putting the book down. <br /><br />I can't wait to start the last book of the trilogy.</span>
